an associated press story friday concerning 
the recall of 1600 randonneur bicycles which may have 
defective front forks contained erroneous information about how to 
identify the model years involved and an incorrect telephone number 
for consumers to call 
only those bicycles that do not have a letter b on the fork 
crown are subject to the recall the correct number for owners to 
call to check whether their bicycles are involved is 18006696400 
