<TEXT>
stock priced bounced higher monday morning despite 
deepening tension in the middle east while the dollar inched up 
against the yen 
the dollar closed the morning session at 14752 yen up 017 yen 
from fridays finish it opened at 14775 yen and fluctuated 
between 14735 and 14777 
the benchmark nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues opened 
lower but rebounded in late morning trading to 2692077 up 13405 
points or 050 percent from fridays close the index had lost 
76272 points on friday 
on the bond market the no 119 10year japanese government bond 
was quoted at 8325 points at 1115 am 1015 pm sunday edt 
up from fridays close of 8321 the yield was 805 percent down 
from 806 percent 
the dollar which normally firms in times of international 
crisis has now gained 087 yen since iraq invaded kuwait on aug 2 
traders said the dollar would remain stronger with the mideast 
tension ongoing 
share prices bounced in thin trading late morning fully 
recovering losses made early in the session indexlinked buying 
helped lift the prices dealers said 
in the first section an estimated 110 million shares changed 
hands down from 170 million shares friday morning 
losing issues outnumbered winning issues 532 to 302 while 208 
issues remained unchanged 
meanwhile north sea brent crude oil for october delivery was 
valued at 272720 a barrel up from fridays 26102620 
</TEXT>
