<TEXT>
about 120 troops stationed in saudi arabia are 
sitting in the front seat of armageddon without weapons or 
equipment for chemical warfare an noncommissioned officer said 
saturday 
i want to have a fighting chance i dont have that said 
air force master sgt johnnie bratton in a phone interview from 
dhahran on saturday night im ready to go out and do whatever i 
have to do but i dont have the minimum protection that is 
required 
the thousands of american servicemen recently deployed to saudi 
arabia are equipped for chemical warfare but those who have been 
there for months are not he said 
bratton a vietnam veteran who has been in the military for 19 
years said the persian gulf situation could evolve into another 
long conflict and troops should be protected every way possible 
were in the front seat of armaggedon he said 
bratton of san marcos said he and 120 other troops have been 
based at dhahran about 165 miles south of kuwait for up to two 
years on training missions he said his unit was composed of air 
force army and navy personnel and that he was based in grand 
forks nd declining to disclose further details 
bratton said he decided to speak to the news media after pleas 
to his superiors congressional leaders and others failed 
the pentagon had no immediate comment saturday night 
i dont have any knowledge of that said pentagon spokesman 
lt col stuart wagner 
