<TEXT>
the un security council on saturday 
unanimously demanded that iraq let all foreigners leave and the 
us ambassador accused baghdad of holding them hostage 
concern about thousands of americans west europeans and 
japanese trapped in iraq and kuwait heightened after iraq said 
friday foreigners from aggressive nations would be used as 
defensive shields for iraqi military installations 
on saturday iraq said some foreigners were moved to strategic 
installations around the country 
it also said the foreigners including babies and the elderly 
would be among the first to suffer the privations of the 
unordered embargo on iraq 
in its resolution saturday the security council demands that 
iraq permit and facilitate the immediate departure from kuwait and 
iraq of the nationals of third countries and grant immediate and 
continuing access of consular officials to such nationals 
the resolution also demands that iraq take no action to 
jeopardize the safety security or health of such nationals 
all 15 members of the council voted for the resolution yemen 
the only arab nation on the council voted for the resolution but 
its ambassador mohamed a sallam said food should be allowed into 
iraq 
the un sanctions allow food and medicine shipments to iraq for 
humanitarian purposes 
meanwhile un secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar 
dispatched two senior un officials to baghdad to urge iraqi 
officials to safeguard the foreigners and let them leave 
earlier saturday us ambassador thomas r pickering denounced 
the latest moves by iraqi president saddam hussein 
we are now responding to the three steps which saddam hussein 
has taken in the last 24 hours including beginning a process of 
sequestering foreign nationals the announcement that he was going 
to use them as military shields and finally the statement this 
morning in which it was clear he was going to hold hostage all 
foreigners 
us officials had previously avoided using the word hostage 
to describe the americans and other foreigners trapped since the 
aug 2 iraqi invasion of kuwait 
asked if he was aware of anyone being harmed or in danger in 
iraq or occupied kuwait pickering said the united states was 
concerned about people who might need routine medical treatment 
iraqi ambassador abdul amir alanbari speaking before the 
security council said the economic embargo of his country is 
unjust and called the us blockade of food and medicines 
to iraqis a terrorist act 
iraq will not prevent foreign nationals from obtaining 
foodstuffs and medicines it will share with foreign nationals what 
comes in alanbari said 
the representative of the ousted kuwaiti government mohammad 
saad al sallal told the council the resolution addresses a 
situation unprecedented in the whole history of the international 
community the taking thousands rather millions of citzens of 
many countries as ransom 
saturdays resolution was the fourth passed by the council 
condemning iraq since the invasion the council previously 
denounced the iraqi invasion imposed the trade embargo and 
rejected the annexation of kuwait 
in the resolution the council again declared the annexation of 
kuwait null and void and therefore demands that the government 
of iraq rescind its orders for the closure of diplomatic and 
consular missions in kuwait and the withdrawal of the immunity of 
their personnel 
iraq has ordered all embassies in kuwait to close claiming the 
country is now part of iraq and diplomats should only be accredited 
in baghdad 
un spokesman fred eckhard said perez de cuellar is sending two 
undersecretarygenerals to baghdad to discuss freedom of movement 
for the foreigners in iraq and kuwait 
the two un officials whom he did not name are expected to 
arrive in baghdad early monday 
the baghdad government holds 3000 americans 4000 britons and 
about 14000 other westerners among the more than 2 million 
foreigners caught in iraq and kuwait when iraq invaded kuwait 
thousands of arabs east europeans and soviets and asians have been 
allowed to cross into jordan 
a usled multinational force and an arab force have been 
deployed to keep iraq from attacking saudi arabia and to impose the 
trade embargo on iraq 
a statement read over iraqi television and radio saturday 
referred to the usled quarantine as an act of war and said 
that as food and medicine become scarce supplies will be set aside 
for the military 
were outraged ambassador sir crispin tickell of britain 
said earlier saturday its almost incredible something like that 
could happen 
</TEXT>
