<TEXT>
a chronology of key dates in the central park 
jogger case 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
april 19 the female jogger out for an evening run is 
brutally attacked raped and left for dead in central park 
april 20 the badly battered woman comatose and suffering from 
hypothermia is discovered and rushed to metropolitan hospital her 
prognosis for recovery is pessimistic police say a gang of 
teenagers out for a night of wilding was responsible 
april 23 suspects are arraigned a prosecutor says seven of 
eight suspects made incriminating statements to police about the 
attack 
april 26 yusef salaam and raymond santana are indicted on 
charges of rape and attempted murder 
april 27 kharey wise antron mccray and steven lopez are 
indicted on charges of rape and attempted murder jermaine robinson 
is indicted for attack on a male jogger in the park clarence 
thomas 14 released with no charges brought 
april 28 kevin richardson is indicted on charges of rape and 
attempted murder parks commissioner henry stern announces 
wideranging plans to improve central park security 
may 1 joggers condition improves enough to give a nurse a 
high five 
may 3 jogger emerges from coma whispers hello to her 
brother 
may 17 the jogger undergoes surgery to repair her shattered 
face 
june 7 she is transferred to gaylord hospital in wallingford 
conn for physical and mental rehabilitation 
oct 5 jermaine robinson 15 pleads guilty to robbery in 
attack on a male jogger the same night of the rapeassault 
oct 9 genetic evidence tested by the fbi turns up no link to 
the halfdozen rape suspects 
nov 14 the jogger is released from gaylord hospital after a 
miraculous recovery 
nov 27 she returns to her job at salomon brothers on wall 
street 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 1 the jogger is promoted to a vice president at salomon 
brothers 
feb 23 state supreme court justice thomas galligan rules the 
suspects statements to police the day of their arrests are 
admissible at trial 
march 16 the case is split into two trials with antron 
mccray yusef salaam and raymond santana the first three defendants 
to be tried 
may 30 michael briscoe pleads guilty to separate attack on the 
night of the jogger rape 
june 13 jury selection begins 
june 25 opening arguments in the trial 
july 16 the jogger in a 12minute appearance on the witness 
stand details the lasting injuries of the attack amnesia lack of 
balance no sense of smell 
aug 1 defendant yusef salaam over the objection of two 
defense lawyers takes the stand and declares his innocence 
aug 6 salaams mother sharonne is ejected from the 
courtroom after an outburst in which she calls one prosecutor a 
liar in the presence of the jury 
aug 7 defense closing arguments 
aug 8 prosecution closing 
aug 9 jury begins deliberating 
aug 18 the three defendants are convicted of rape and assault 
and acquitted of the top count of attempted murder 
</TEXT>
