skills 36 percent said men were better drivers 28 percent 
responded that women were better and 4 percent didnt know 
fiftyfive percent of those surveyed were women and 45 percent were 
men 
the nationwide poll was conducted through random telephone calls 
during june by fleishmanhillard research inc of st louis its 
reported margin of error was 4 to 6 percentage points 
the 10 trueorfalse questions on driving safety and accident 
avoidance included ones on where and when most traffic deaths occur 
