bf skinner one of the centurys 
leading psychologists who believed human behavior could be 
engineered to build a better world died saturday of leukemia at 
age 86 
he was the patriarch of the school of thought known as 
behaviorism and the inventor of the skinner box a tool he used 
to demonstrate his theory that rewarded behavior is repeated 
while remembered by many and sometimes scorned for teaching 
pigeons to play pingpong and guide missiles his book walden 
two was required reading for a generation of college students in 
the 1960s and 1970s 
burrhus frederic skinner views were based on his principle of 
operant behavior the idea that seemingly spontaneous action is 
regulated through rewards and punishment 
many psychologists disagreed with his theories 
but his application of the ideas of the russian physiologist 
ivan pavlov left an indelible stamp on american society parents 
use his operant conditioning each time they praise a behavior 
they want and punish one they dont want 
he died at mount auburn hospital in cambridge 
