of rain early monday and the national weather service issued a 
flash flood watch 
leaks appeared in the dam on saturday after six inches of rain 
pushed the lake about two feet above flood stage the lake rose at 
about one inch per hour until cresting at 1 pm sunday fulton 
county conservation officer dick eurit said 
at least 100 people were evacuated from the area immediately 
below the dam officials said 
other residents of the lightly populated area below the dam were 
advised to leave their homes or prepare to evacuate if the dam were 
to break said fulton county chief jailer robert bryant 
twentyeight patients at woodlawn hospital were dismissed taken 
to other hospitals nursing homes or the local high school 
gymnasium shortly after midnight officials said 
volunteers fire crews and civil defense officials laid about 
13000 sand bags along the dam early sunday bryant said 
its holding at this point our main problem is now were 
expecting another 2 to 3 inches of rainfall tonight he said 
sunday afternoon 
the us army corps of engineers brought large pumps to attempt 
to lower the lake the national weather service said 
lake manitou is about 12 feet above mill creek which flows 
along the eastern edge of rochester a town of 5000 in 
northcentral indiana and empties into the tippecanoe river 
a complete failure of the dam could raise mill creek by 6 feet 
the weather service said it would crest in rochester within a half 
hour of a dam failure 
the biggest problem it would affect would be our hospital if 
the dam was to go out a large quantity of water would hit it he 
said 
a similar threat faced the westcentral wisconsin town of tomah 
on saturday about 1500 people evacuated when high water 
threatened to rupture the lake tomah dam on the lemonweir river 
about 700 people stayed out of their homes during the night but 
began returning sunday 
but flowing though the gates of the dam raised the level of the 
